(37, 'researcher', 39, 'Judercio Jose Nhauche is a Student Intern at Brandeis University. I am a student Intern Their research focuses on Food Security, Nutrition & Health, Markets & Trade. Key topics include: food security.', 'auto-generated', '', 0, 0, '2026-05-19 13:21:37'),
(38, 'researcher', 40, 'Judercio Jose Nhauche is a student and Professor at Brandeis University with research interests spanning food security, nutrition and health, and markets and trade. His work focuses on forecasting food insecurity, shocks, and vulnerabilities, as well as understanding trade networks and shock propagation across global contexts, including Africa. He is open to co-advising students working at the intersection of technology and food systems.', 'claude-sonnet-4-6', 'd2d2a99eadf0bf4838601173c18350fc2784be358782f5282eb69a234f13b5d9', 176, 101, '2026-05-19 15:50:05'),
(40, 'researcher', 41, 'Judercio Jose Nhauche is an intern at Brandeis University with a focus on food security, nutrition and health, and the intersection of technology with food systems. His work explores food challenges that require cross-sector solutions beyond the food system itself, with a regional emphasis on Asia, including China. Judercio is open to co-advising and available to work with students across relevant subject areas.', 'claude-sonnet-4-6', '088af3add1d6c378dcf2bca0eaa3d86bd0410bc8047b7a71426c8dda3a7f88df', 147, 99, '2026-05-19 18:32:52'),
(42, 'researcher', 42, 'Greg Sixt is a Director, FACT Alliance at MIT. Qualitative social science researcher focused on food systems transitions, innovation systems, and water governance Their research focuses on Food Security, Nutrition & Health, Ecosystems & Biodiversity, Governance & Innovation, Markets & Trade, Crosscutting Themes. Key topics include: agricultural innovation systems, water governance.', 'auto-generated', '', 0, 0, '2026-05-19 18:54:31'),
(43, 'researcher', 43, 'Romario Joao Manuel is a Student at Havard. I am student at Harvard university with 10 years of work experience Their research focuses on Food Security, Nutrition & Health. Key topics include: food security, tech food systems.', 'auto-generated', '', 0, 0, '2026-05-19 19:57:53'),
(44, 'researcher', 44, 'Maria Santos is a Research Scientist at the University of São Paulo specializing in climate adaptation within smallholder farming systems. Her work focuses on the intersections of climate change, agricultural adaptation, and food security, with a regional emphasis on Brazil and South America. She is currently open to research collaborations and funding opportunities aligned with her expertise in climate-resilient agriculture.', 'claude-sonnet-4-6', '547e2ffaee67bf04358afbdb100983c288907540284f68ccbda4573e90074e00', 122, 83, '2026-05-19 23:38:46'),
(45, 'researcher', 45, 'Ahmed Hassan is a Director at the University of Khartoum with a research focus on water management, transboundary rivers, and transboundary water governance. His work is geographically concentrated in Africa, the Middle East, and Sudan, addressing critical regional challenges related to shared water resources and governance frameworks. He is not currently open to co-advising opportunities.', 'claude-sonnet-4-6', '2db1103b3d1f486774a778540617fcc9db696016143875a5836c837c69e6b2cc', 123, 86, '2026-05-19 23:38:48'),
(46, 'researcher', 46, 'Lisa Chen is an Associate Professor at National Taiwan University whose research focuses on sustainable water and energy systems, with particular expertise in the water-energy nexus. Her work is centered on water, energy, and sustainability challenges within the East Asian and Taiwanese regional context.', 'claude-sonnet-4-6', '617a182fce793022b0dc20d900752704db20aa3c534195046ea233f9cc5d42f2', 119, 61, '2026-05-19 23:38:50'),
(47, 'researcher', 47, 'Emmanuel Kofi is a Senior Lecturer at the University of Ghana specializing in malaria vector control and epidemiology, with a focus on mosquito-borne disease control in Ghana and West Africa. His research addresses malaria prevention and health outcomes within African contexts. He is not currently open to co-advising arrangements.', 'claude-sonnet-4-6', '1338b8abe3dcc7cb32ee87806c88ddff867057628a77a8f1b6a28d0d01fe9bda', 128, 76, '2026-05-19 23:38:53'),
(48, 'researcher', 48, 'Sofia Petrov is a Professor at Moscow State University specializing in Arctic ecosystem changes, adaptation, and the impacts of climate change on Arctic communities. Her research spans the intersecting areas of climate, environment, and biodiversity, with a geographic focus on Europe, Russia, and the Arctic region.', 'claude-sonnet-4-6', '1e28c7f4bdc14a275dcd1af3081c768252cb5e8e63ff74f9f8657e94f44ff04f', 119, 68, '2026-05-19 23:38:54'),
(49, 'researcher', 49, 'Carlos Mendoza is a Research Fellow at the National Autonomous University of Mexico specializing in forest conservation and indigenous knowledge, with a focus on indigenous forest management practices. His work spans environmental, biodiversity, and innovation topics within Mexico, Latin America, and the broader Americas region. He is not currently available for co-advising engagements.', 'claude-sonnet-4-6', '72c739a3379c35dd3d0b08e7f8c3c9c9379f2fee91aa5b6986d65de605d4c92d', 122, 79, '2026-05-19 23:38:57'),
(50, 'researcher', 50, 'Amara Diallo is a Lecturer at Cheikh Anta Diop University whose research focuses on women entrepreneurs operating within agricultural value chains, with a particular emphasis on gender dynamics in agriculture business. Based in Senegal, their work spans West Africa and addresses themes of gender, agriculture, and economic development. Diallo is open to research collaborations and funding opportunities aligned with these focus areas.', 'claude-sonnet-4-6', 'af350fc8114217e154aded99106504e28e381765d28f53147fd74a250615cc5d', 131, 93, '2026-05-19 23:39:00'),
(51, 'researcher', 51, 'Rajesh Sharma is an Assistant Professor at the Indian Institute of Technology Delhi whose research focuses on the sustainable intensification of agriculture, with an emphasis on crop productivity and sustainability. His work addresses the intersecting challenges of agriculture, nutrition, and poverty, with a geographic concentration on India and South Asia. He is currently not open to co-advising arrangements.', 'claude-sonnet-4-6', '4a7d8d33a26c424bba8a884049fd483e1579b77b680a4672d31ffa01a2776904', 123, 81, '2026-05-19 23:39:02'),
(52, 'researcher', 52, 'Fatima Al-Rashid is an Associate Professor at the American University of Beirut whose research focuses on food security in conflict zones and crisis food systems. Her work engages with questions of governance and resilience, with a geographic emphasis on Lebanon and the broader Middle East.', 'claude-sonnet-4-6', '4dfee8138314a6bdd8aa17b2d8d3b7ba3c437ca3725830ca722f56f5e7cf19bf', 125, 66, '2026-05-19 23:39:04'),
(53, 'researcher', 53, 'David Okonkwo is a researcher at the University of Nairobi specializing in renewable energy innovation and off-grid energy solutions for rural communities in Kenya and East Africa. His work sits at the intersection of energy access, technological innovation, and poverty reduction. He is currently focused on advancing sustainable energy systems in underserved areas across the region.', 'claude-sonnet-4-6', 'bed4b22f33f9e5812708da989a681239374e9837e44deb61dcae0698a9b153e7', 127, 81, '2026-05-19 23:39:06'),
(54, 'researcher', 54, 'Elena Volkova is a Senior Scientist at Saint Petersburg State University specializing in marine biodiversity conservation and ocean ecosystem protection. Her research focuses on biodiversity, environmental science, and conservation, with a geographic emphasis on Europe and Russia. She is currently not open to co-advising opportunities.', 'claude-sonnet-4-6', '1d606bc7cb43bed594301bfbf267b8478f43509dbccd0795427baf6fea048048', 117, 68, '2026-05-19 23:39:08'),
(55, 'researcher', 55, 'Juan Rivera serves as Research Director at the Pontifical Catholic University of Peru, where his work centers on nutrition, food security, and food systems within mountain communities across Peru and Latin America. His research addresses highland food production and its intersections with poverty reduction in Andean contexts. He is not currently available for co-advising arrangements.', 'claude-sonnet-4-6', '2f8503e580ff01a7ebb29d0b8807348e1a1bf9a05f1a4f1dddaf967de812aa4b', 124, 77, '2026-05-19 23:39:10'),
(56, 'researcher', 56, 'Maria Santos is a Research Scientist at the University of São Paulo specializing in climate adaptation within smallholder farming systems. Her work focuses on the intersection of climate change, agricultural adaptation, and food security, with a regional emphasis on Brazil and South America. She is not currently open to co-advising arrangements.', 'claude-sonnet-4-6', '547e2ffaee67bf04358afbdb100983c288907540284f68ccbda4573e90074e00', 122, 72, '2026-05-19 23:39:12'),
(57, 'researcher', 57, 'Ahmed Hassan is a Director at the University of Khartoum with a research focus on water management, transboundary rivers, and transboundary water governance. His work spans the Africa, Middle East, and Sudan regions, addressing critical issues related to shared water resources and governance frameworks.', 'claude-sonnet-4-6', '2db1103b3d1f486774a778540617fcc9db696016143875a5836c837c69e6b2cc', 123, 69, '2026-05-19 23:39:14'),
(58, 'researcher', 58, 'Lisa Chen is an Associate Professor at National Taiwan University whose research focuses on sustainable water and energy systems, with a particular emphasis on the water-energy nexus. Her work is geographically centered on Taiwan and the broader East Asia region, addressing critical sustainability challenges at the intersection of water and energy resources.', 'claude-sonnet-4-6', '617a182fce793022b0dc20d900752704db20aa3c534195046ea233f9cc5d42f2', 119, 69, '2026-05-19 23:39:17'),
(59, 'researcher', 59, 'Emmanuel Kofi is a Senior Lecturer at the University of Ghana specializing in malaria vector control and epidemiology, with a research focus on mosquito-borne disease control in Ghana and West Africa. His work addresses critical public health challenges related to malaria and infectious disease in the African context.', 'claude-sonnet-4-6', '1338b8abe3dcc7cb32ee87806c88ddff867057628a77a8f1b6a28d0d01fe9bda', 128, 71, '2026-05-19 23:39:19'),
(60, 'researcher', 60, 'Sofia Petrov is a Professor at Moscow State University specializing in Arctic ecosystem changes, adaptation, and the impacts of climate change on Arctic communities. Her research spans climate, environment, and biodiversity with a geographic focus on Europe, Russia, and the Arctic region.', 'claude-sonnet-4-6', '1e28c7f4bdc14a275dcd1af3081c768252cb5e8e63ff74f9f8657e94f44ff04f', 119, 62, '2026-05-19 23:39:21'),
(61, 'researcher', 61, 'Carlos Mendoza is a Research Fellow at the National Autonomous University of Mexico specializing in forest conservation and indigenous knowledge systems, with a focus on indigenous forest management practices. His work spans environmental, biodiversity, and innovation themes across Mexico and the broader Latin American context. He is not currently open to co-advising opportunities.', 'claude-sonnet-4-6', '72c739a3379c35dd3d0b08e7f8c3c9c9379f2fee91aa5b6986d65de605d4c92d', 122, 75, '2026-05-19 23:39:23'),
(62, 'researcher', 62, 'Amara Diallo is a Lecturer at Cheikh Anta Diop University whose research focuses on women entrepreneurs operating within agricultural value chains, with a particular emphasis on gender dynamics in agribusiness. Their work engages with themes of gender, agriculture, and economic development, situated primarily in Senegal and the broader West African context.', 'claude-sonnet-4-6', 'af350fc8114217e154aded99106504e28e381765d28f53147fd74a250615cc5d', 131, 81, '2026-05-19 23:39:25'),
(63, 'researcher', 63, 'Rajesh Sharma is an Assistant Professor at the Indian Institute of Technology Delhi whose research focuses on the sustainable intensification of agriculture, with an emphasis on crop productivity and sustainability. His work addresses the intersecting challenges of agriculture, nutrition, and poverty across South Asia, with a particular focus on India. He is currently not open to co-advising arrangements.', 'claude-sonnet-4-6', '4a7d8d33a26c424bba8a884049fd483e1579b77b680a4672d31ffa01a2776904', 123, 81, '2026-05-19 23:39:28'),
(64, 'researcher', 64, 'Fatima Al-Rashid is an Associate Professor at the American University of Beirut whose research centers on food security in conflict zones and crisis food systems, with a regional focus on the Middle East and Lebanon. Her work engages with questions of governance and resilience as they relate to food systems under conditions of instability and crisis. She is open to research collaborations and funding opportunities aligned with her expertise in conflict-affected food environments.', 'claude-sonnet-4-6', '4dfee8138314a6bdd8aa17b2d8d3b7ba3c437ca3725830ca722f56f5e7cf19bf', 125, 99, '2026-05-19 23:39:30'),
(65, 'researcher', 65, 'David Okonkwo is a researcher at the University of Nairobi specializing in renewable energy innovation and off-grid energy solutions for rural communities in Kenya and East Africa. His work sits at the intersection of energy access, technological innovation, and poverty reduction. He is currently not open to co-advising arrangements.', 'claude-sonnet-4-6', 'bed4b22f33f9e5812708da989a681239374e9837e44deb61dcae0698a9b153e7', 127, 75, '2026-05-19 23:39:32'),
(66, 'researcher', 66, 'Elena Volkova is a Senior Scientist at Saint Petersburg State University specializing in marine biodiversity conservation and ocean ecosystem protection. Her research focuses on biodiversity, environmental conservation, and ecological topics with a regional emphasis on Europe and Russia. She is available for research collaborations and funding opportunities, though she is not open to co-advising arrangements.', 'claude-sonnet-4-6', '1d606bc7cb43bed594301bfbf267b8478f43509dbccd0795427baf6fea048048', 117, 79, '2026-05-19 23:39:34'),
(67, 'researcher', 67, 'Juan Rivera is a Research Director at the Pontifical Catholic University of Peru specializing in nutrition, food systems, and food security within mountain and highland communities. His work focuses on the intersection of highland food production, poverty, and nutrition across Andean and Latin American contexts. He is currently not open to co-advising arrangements.', 'claude-sonnet-4-6', '2f8503e580ff01a7ebb29d0b8807348e1a1bf9a05f1a4f1dddaf967de812aa4b', 124, 76, '2026-05-19 23:39:37'),
(68, 'researcher', 68, 'Gabriel Nhauche is a Intern at Havard. Intern at MIT focusing on Food Systems Their research focuses on Food Security, Nutrition & Health, Ecosystems & Biodiversity. Key topics include: food security, tech food systems.', 'auto-generated', '', 0, 0, '2026-05-20 17:23:25'),
(69, 'researcher', 69, 'Judercio Jose Nhauche is a Mr at UCT. A researcher Their research focuses on Food Security, Nutrition & Health. Key topics include: food security.', 'auto-generated', '', 0, 0, '2026-05-21 15:44:16'),
(70, 'researcher', 70, 'Judercio Jose Nhauche is a Researcher at UCT. A researcher in the area of technology and Artificial intelligence Their research focuses on Food Security, Nutrition & Health. Key topics include: food security, tech food systems.', 'auto-generated', '', 0, 0, '2026-05-22 20:26:30'),
(71, 'researcher', 71, 'Judercio Jose Nhauche is an intern at MIT\'s J-WAFS (Abdul Latif Jameel Water and Food Systems Lab), focusing on food security, nutrition, and health with an emphasis on food environments and forecasting food insecurity, shocks, and vulnerabilities. His work spans global and Americas-focused contexts, applying technology-driven approaches to food systems research. He is open to co-advising students at any institution and across all geographies.', 'claude-sonnet-4-6', 'e8caab6a2a5400d064f1109649bf741620ba0faf3c7cf5aff877e4ef858c9546', 148, 109, '2026-05-26 03:03:14'),
(72, 'researcher', 72, 'Jaden Nhauche is a Student Intern at Cambridge University. I am a student Intern at MIT Their research focuses on Food Security, Nutrition & Health, Ecosystems & Biodiversity. Key topics include: food security, tech food systems.', 'auto-generated', '', 0, 0, '2026-05-22 20:58:24'),
(74, 'researcher', 73, 'Videnio Jose Joao is a Research Scientist at Oxford University. I am an agricultural researcher specializing in sustainable agriculture, food systems, and climate-smart farming practices. My work focuses on improving crop productivity, strengthening food security, and supporting smallholder farmers through data-driven research and innovative agricultural solutions. I have experience working on projects related to soil health, irrigation, agribusiness, agricultural policy, and rural development across developing and emerging economies. Their research focuses on Food Security, Nutrition & Health, Ecosystems & Biodiversity. Key topics include: food security, tech food systems and others.', 'auto-generated', '', 0, 0, '2026-05-27 00:16:57'),
(75, 'funding_call', 16, 'The USDA NIFA AFRI Foundational and Applied Science Program is the USDA\'s primary competitive agricultural research grant, offering awards ranging from $10,000 to $10,000,000 as part of a $300 million total funding pool. It supports research, extension, or integrated projects across six broad priority areas including plant and animal health, food safety, nutrition, bioenergy, agricultural systems and technology, and rural economics. U.S.-based researchers should note that deadlines vary by priority area and must consult the full Notice of Funding Opportunity (NOFO) for specific submission dates, with a program-wide outer deadline of December 31, 2026.', 'claude-sonnet-4-6', 'b5cfaca743088c7174cc492088afd5d478ea640779e7b003630e7cf39c87b3b5', 322, 157, '2026-06-01 18:44:56'),
(76, 'funding_call', 17, 'The USDA NIFA AFRI Foundational and Applied Science Program is the flagship federal competitive grant program for agricultural research, supporting work across six broad priority areas including plant and animal health, food safety, nutrition, bioenergy, agricultural systems, and rural economics. Awards range widely from $10,000 to $10,000,000, with $300 million in total estimated funding available, and projects can be research-only, extension-only, or integrated combinations of research, education, and extension. The program is open to US-based applicants with international collaboration permitted, but researchers should consult the full Notice of Funding Opportunity (NOFO) directly since deadlines vary by priority area and are not uniform across the program.', 'claude-sonnet-4-6', 'b5cfaca743088c7174cc492088afd5d478ea640779e7b003630e7cf39c87b3b5', 322, 165, '2026-06-01 18:50:17'),
(77, 'funding_call', 18, 'USDA NIFA is offering a single award of $923,325 to build neutral, secure data repositories and cooperatives where farmers, universities, and nonprofits can store and share agricultural data. Priority research areas include farm profitability, soil health, invasive species, new agricultural markets, and precision nutrition and food quality. A wide range of applicants are eligible, including universities, state agricultural experiment stations, private organizations, corporations, federal agencies, and even individuals, with a deadline of June 26, 2026.', 'claude-sonnet-4-6', '0d084d27a16727d4efc35c4c96cc53463c81eefb4bc3b84e110c57bd53195995', 278, 119, '2026-06-01 18:53:52'),
(78, 'funding_call', 19, 'FFAR\'s ROAR program offers grants of up to $250,000 over 1–2 years for rapid research addressing emerging or unanticipated pests and pathogens that threaten U.S. crops or livestock at a regional or national scale. Eligible projects can cover diagnostics, monitoring, mitigation strategies, and pre-outbreak preparedness, with international applicants considered if there is a direct and significant U.S. threat. The application process starts with a one-page concept note, and if selected, a full application must be submitted within 8 weeks, with a final deadline of December 31, 2026.', 'claude-sonnet-4-6', '82f89f3b6ba59bd6168c6a4621b0d45285578d9fc23335882222d31a3c634851', 278, 147, '2026-06-01 19:03:39'),
(81, 'researcher', 75, 'Judercio Nhauche is a Student Intern at Havard University. I am a Master of Science in Business Analytics candidate at Brandeis University and a Research, Data Analytics & Web Development Intern with the FACT Alliance at MIT’s Abdul Latif Jameel Water and Food Systems Lab (J-WAFS). Their research focuses on Food Security, Nutrition & Health, Ecosystems & Biodiversity. Key topics include: food security, tech food systems.', 'auto-generated', '', 0, 0, '2026-06-05 13:18:20'),
(82, 'researcher', 76, 'Judercio Nhauche is a Student Intern at Duke University. I am a Master of Science in Business Analytics candidate at Brandeis University and a Research, Data Analytics & Web Development Intern with the FACT Alliance at MIT’s Abdul Latif Jameel Water and Food Systems Lab (J-WAFS). Their research focuses on Food Security, Nutrition & Health. Key topics include: food security, tech food systems.', 'auto-generated', '', 0, 0, '2026-06-05 13:21:36'),
(83, 'researcher', 77, 'Judercio Nhauche is a Student Intern at Brandeis University. My work focuses on building digital research infrastructure, applying data analytics, and developing platforms that strengthen collaboration among researchers, institutions, and funding organizations in global food and water systems. Their research focuses on Food Security, Nutrition & Health. Key topics include: food security, tech food systems and others.', 'auto-generated', '', 0, 0, '2026-06-05 13:24:25');

